  "id": "guide/understanding-communicating-with-http",
  "title": "Understanding communicating with backend services using HTTP",
  "contents": "\n\n\n\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n  <h1 id=\"understanding-communicating-with-backend-services-using-http\">Understanding communicating with backend services using HTTP<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/understanding-communicating-with-http#understanding-communicating-with-backend-services-using-http\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n<p>Most front-end applications need to communicate with a server over the HTTP protocol, to download or upload data and access other back-end services. Angular provides a client HTTP API for Angular applications, the <code><a href=\"api/common/http/HttpClient\" class=\"code-anchor\">HttpClient</a></code> service class in <code>@angular/common/<a href=\"api/common/http\" class=\"code-anchor\">http</a></code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"prerequisites\">Prerequisites<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/understanding-communicating-with-http#prerequisites\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>Before working with the <code><a href=\"api/common/http/HttpClientModule\" class=\"code-anchor\">HttpClientModule</a></code>, you should have a basic understanding of the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>TypeScript programming</li>\n<li>Usage of the HTTP protocol</li>\n<li>Angular application-design fundamentals, as described in <a href=\"guide/architecture\">Angular Concepts</a></li>\n<li>Observable techniques and operators.\nSee the <a href=\"guide/observables\">Observables guide</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"http-client-service-features\">HTTP client service features<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/understanding-communicating-with-http#http-client-service-features\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>The HTTP client service offers the following major features.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The ability to request <a href=\"guide/http-request-data-from-server\">typed response objects</a></li>\n<li>Streamlined <a href=\"guide/http-handle-request-errors\">error handling</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"guide/http-test-requests\">Testability</a> features</li>\n<li>Request and response <a href=\"guide/http-intercept-requests-and-responses\">interception</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"whats-next\">What's next<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/understanding-communicating-with-http#whats-next\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"guide/http-setup-server-communication\">Setup for server communication</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n  <div class=\"reviewed\">Last reviewed on Wed Aug 16 2023</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/common/http\n - api/common/http/HttpClient\n - guide/architecture-next-steps\n - guide/developer-guide-overview\n - guide/docs-style-guide\n - guide/example-apps-list\n - guide/http-server-communication\n - guide/npm-packages\n - guide/pipes\n - guide/rx-library\n - guide/testing-components-scenarios\n - guide/what-is-angular\n - start/start-data\n - tutorial/tour-of-heroes/toh-pt4\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - api/common/http\n - api/common/http/HttpClient\n - api/common/http/HttpClientModule\n - guide/architecture\n - guide/http-handle-request-errors\n - guide/http-intercept-requests-and-responses\n - guide/http-request-data-from-server\n - guide/http-setup-server-communication\n - guide/http-test-requests\n - guide/observables\n - guide/understanding-communicating-with-http#http-client-service-features\n - guide/understanding-communicating-with-http#prerequisites\n - guide/understanding-communicating-with-http#understanding-communicating-with-backend-services-using-http\n - guide/understanding-communicating-with-http#whats-next\n-->"
